The paper proposes a new framework for using Q-learning in continuous action spaces, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. The paper also discusses the use of Q-learning in robotics and control (cs.RO, cs.SY), which are relevant sub-categories for this work. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the Cross Entropy Method (CEM), which is a common optimization method in machine learning and optimization (cs.MA).
